HEADWORD: Tolutation
<hw>Tol`u*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tolutim</ets> on a trot, properly, lifting up the feet, akin to
<ets>tollere</ets> to lift up.]</ety> <def>A pacing or ambling.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

